<FILEID>AP-NR-04-17-89 0046EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r i PM-Malaysia-Ads     04-17 0201</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Malaysia-Ads,0206</SECOND>
<HEAD>Government Banning TV Ads That Show Only Non-Malaysians</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The government is banning racy
television advertisements and commercials that show only
non-Malaysian models, the information minister said in an interview
published today.
   Beginning July 1, Caucasian and other non-Malaysian models can
continue to appear in commercials only if the ads also include
Malays, Chinese, Indians or other races that predominate in
Malaysia, said Information Minister Mohamed Rahmat.
   ``We have told advertisers that if the cast is a mix of
Caucasian, Pan-Asian and some of the multi-racial groups in
Malaysia, we will allow the commercials to appear,'' Rahmat said in
an interview published in the New Straits Times daily.
   Commercials with women in swimsuits and scanty clothing will
also be banned in this country Islam where is the official religion.
   Of the country's three TV channels, two are owned by the
government and the other belongs to the ruling party.
   Michael Tang, Association of Accredited Advertising Agents of
Malaysia President, said the ban was ``a little too harsh and
debatable'' and called for the review of the ban.
   Malaysia's 17 million population is 55 percent Malay and 37
percent Chinese, with the remainder mainly Indian.
</TEXT>
