<FIRST>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     04-17 0440</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0453</SECOND>
<HEAD>Cold, Snow Pushes Into Northern States</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   A cold front driving into the nation's midsection spread rain
and thunderstorms from Nebraska to the lower Great Lakes and
produced light snow further north.
   Temperatures dropped sharply in some northern states as cold
Canadian air moved down behind the front. Readings early today were
in the teens and 20s from western Montana to northern Minnesota.
   Light snow accompanied the cold in parts of Minnesota, South
Dakota, Wyoming and Montana.
   Further south, the front produced rain and thunderstorms in
western Nebraska, southern Minnesota and parts of the lower Great
Lakes.
   Thunderstorms were widely scattered over eastern and central
Oklahoma.
   Low pressure off the coast of northern New England continued to
produce light rain over Maine.
   Fog covered much of the Gulf and Atlantic coasts.
   Today's forecast called for scattered showers from the Great
Lakes and northern Ohio Valley across southern Minnesota, the
middle Mississippi Valley, Nebraska and northern Colorado; a few
thunderstorms from eastern Oklahoma and Arkansas to lower Michigan,
and in southern Florida; and rain mixed with wet snow from eastern
South Dakota into the central Rockies and in eastern Upper Michigan.
   Highs were forecast to be in the 30s from eastern North Dakota
across northern Minnesota into western Upper Michigan; 40s and 50s
in northern Maine, from lower Michigan across the northern Plains
to the northern Rockies; 80s from the middle and southern Atlantic
Coast across Florida, the Gulf Coast, the lower Mississippi Valley,
much of the southern Plains, the southern Rockies, northern Arizona
and Nevada to inland California; 90s across the Desert Southwest
and southwest Texas. Highs elsewhere were expected to be in the 60s
and 70s.
   Temperatures at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 18 degrees at Williston,
N.D., and Havre, Mont., to 82 degrees at Las Vegas.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 52 fair; Boston 42 fair; Buffalo 43 partly
cloudy; Charleston, S.C. 53 fair; Cincinnati 53 partly cloudy;
Cleveland 54 cloudy; Detroit 55 cloudy; Miami 74 partly cloudy; New
York 45 fair; Philadelphia 42 foggy; Pittsburgh 47 partly cloudy;
Portland, Maine 40 partly cloudy; Washington 45 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 19 fair; Chicago 60 partly cloudy;
Dallas-Fort Worth 63 fair; Denver 47 drizzle; Des Moines 53 partly
cloudy; Indianapolis 57 cloudy; Kansas City 60 fair;
Minneapolis-St. Paul 39 windy; Nashville 57 fair; New Orleans 54
foggy; St. Louis 66 partly cloudy.
   _West: Albuquerque 51 fair; Anchorage 35 cloudy; Las Vegas 75
cloudy; Los Angeles 60 cloudy; Phoenix 75 fair; Salt Lake City 49
fair; San Diego 61 cloudy; San Francisco 55 cloudy; Seattle 41 fair.
   _Canada: Montreal 30 foggy; Toronto 41 partly cloudy.
</TEXT>
