<FIRST>r i PM-Romania-Asylum     04-17 0165</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Romania-Asylum,0172</SECOND>
<HEAD>Romanian Table Tennis Official Requests Asylum</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FRANKFURT, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The head of Romania's national
table tennis team has requested political asylum in West Germany,
officials said today.
   Ella Zeller-Constantinescu, a former world champion who also is
vice president of the European Table Tennis Union, defected after
the table tennis World Championship in Dortmund.
   After the event ended April 9, she refused to return to Romania
and entered a refugee camp in Friedland, where she applied for
political asylum, said camp officials who requested anonymity.
   Another Romanian sportswoman today was reported missing in
Rennes, France, where she participated in a swim meet. Police said
they had not excluded the possibility she intended to seek
political asylum.
   Livia Capariu, 16, who recently clocked world-class performances
in the Romanian national freestyle championship, was reported
missing just before her team left for Bucharest, police told the
French news agency Agence France-Presse.
   Team officials told police they searched without turning up any
trace of her.
</TEXT>
