<HEAD>Three Arrested Trying to Smuggle Exotic Birds</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MELBOURNE, Australia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three West Germans were arrested
Monday for trying to smuggle out of the country 32 exotic birds
worth about $150,000, police said.
   The three were taken into custody as they were boarding a flight
to Singapore, said police commander Nigel Hadgkiss.
   The birds had been drugged and placed in tubular wire mesh cages
inside a suitcase, he said, adding that police also recovered a
