<HEAD>WASHN: in legislation.</HEAD>
<BYLINE>C. Calendar Year 1981</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   The record indicates that in calendar year 1981, Representative
Wright received a gift of free housing valued at $3,279 arising out
of his free use of apartments located at 4212-C Hulen Place, Fort
Worth, Texas, and 1067 Roaring Springs Road, Fort Worth, Texas, and
each controlled by George Mallick, an individual the committee has
reason to believe had a direct interest in legislation.
   Because this gift to Representative Wright was not reported on
his financial disclosure statement for calendar year 1981 as
required by House Rule XLIV, the committee has reason to believe
that Representative Wright violated House Rule XLIV and House Rule
XLIII, clause 4, the latter of which imposes a limit of $100 on
gifts received from persons with a direct interest in legislation.
</TEXT>
