<FIRST>u a AM-OverweightNurse     04-17 0131</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Overweight Nurse,0134</SECOND>
<HEAD>Jury Finds Private College Wrongfully Dismissed Student For Obesity</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PROVIDENCE, R.I. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A private Roman Catholic college
wrongfully dismissed a nursing student when it forced her to leave
the college because she could not lose weight, a federal jury ruled
Monday.
   The jury ordered Salve Regina College in Newport to pay Sharon
Russell $30,000 for her tuition and wages she was deprived of while
she completed her nursing degree at a school in Hartford, Conn.
   Russell, 24, now a nurse in St. Petersburg, Fla., maintained she
was coerced into signing a contract with the college in her junior
year stating that she would lose two pounds a week.
   The school would not allow her to return in the fall of 1985 and
complete her senior year.
</TEXT>
