<HEAD>Egypt to Help Search For Missing Israeli Soldiers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CAIRO, Egypt (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Egypt on Monday offered to help locate the
bodies of 19 Israeli soldiers reported missing in the 1973 Middle
East war, an Israeli official said.
   Gen. Reuven Merhav, the director of Israel's Foreign Ministry,
also told journalists he invited Egyptian Foreign Minister Esmat
Abdel-Meguid to visit his country. Abdel-Meguid accepted the
invitation but no date has yet been set for the visit, an Egyptian
Foreign Ministry source said.
   Merhav has been in Cairo since Thursday for talks on bilateral
questions, including a renewed effort to locate the missing bodies,
the source said.
   About 400 Israeli soldiers were reported missing in Egypt
following the 1973 fighting on the Sinai peninsula. The bodies of
all but 19 were recovered.
