   Similarly, when Moncrief agreed in June 1984 to take a ``farm
out'' from Wright of Wright's interest in the drilling of a second
Williams well (i.e., a buy-out of most of Wright's interest in the
well), the terms of the ``farm out'' were in accordance with
industry custom and the price was at or near market value. Thus
there was no gift to Wright; nor can either the repurchase or the
``farm out,'' which both took place in 1984, reasonably be viewed
as compenation to Wright for his efforts on Neptune's behalf in
1979.
   As discussed in full in Section III. A. of this Report, Wright's
receipt of the gift in excess of $100 from Moncrief violates House
Rule XLIII, clauses 1 and 4; and consideration 5 of the Code of
Ethics for Government Service. His failure to disclose the gift
violates House Rule XLIV.
