<FIRST>r f PM-Coastal-TexasEastern     04-17 0171</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Coastal-Texas Eastern,0177</SECOND>
<HEAD>Coastal Extends Tender Offer for Texas Eastern</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Coastal Corp. extended its $2.6 billion tender
offer today for Texas Eastern Corp.'s outstanding stock despite an
agreement between Texas Eastern and a rival suitor.
   The offer and withdrawal period will now expire at midnight May
5, unless it is further extended, a Coastal statement said. About
43,326 shares have been tendered to date, the statement said.
   The battle for Texas Eastern began Jan. 16 when Houston-based
Coastal announced its surprise takeover bid. But the Texas Eastern
board rejected the bid as too low, signing a merger agreement
instead with Panhandle Eastern Corp. on Feb. 21.
   Panhandle Eastern's $3.2 billion offer includes provisions to
buy up to 80 percent of Texas Eastern's 60.8 million outstanding
shares and a stock exchange at the same $53-a-share value for the
remaining shares.
   The combination of the two Houston-based natural gas companies
would create a 27,000-mile system and result in one of the nation's
largest pipeline companies in terms of miles.
</TEXT>
