<FIRST>u f BC-BritishStocks 1stLd-Writethru   04-17 0209</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-British Stocks, 1st Ld-Writethru,0216</SECOND>
<HEAD>London Shares Mixed</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: UPDATES with closing prices</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices on the London Stock Exchange closed
mixed Monday in lackluster trading.
   At the close the Financial Times 100-share index was up 1.1
points, or .05 percent, at 2054.7.
   The narrower Financial Times 30-share index was down 4.9 points
at 1686.1, reflecting losses by several major capitalized stocks.
Volume was thin, as 468.1 million shares changed hands, compared
with Friday's 648.1 million shares.
   Shares got off to a buoyant start on the back of continued
enthusiasm following Friday's rally in London and on Wall Street.
But the positive tone wore thin as participants steered clear of
the market and as doubts about the underlying health of the British
economy returned.
   ``There's a general degree of uncertainty'' about the British
economic picture, said one trader.
   A major worry at the moment is whether higher wage settlements
will add to inflationary pressures, he added.
   There was little reaction to news that British retail sales in
March were unchanged in volume terms from the previous month, while
rising 4.7 percent from a year earlier.
   While perhaps signaling a slowing of consumer demand, the
provisional figures could be revised significantly in coming weeks,
dealers said.
</TEXT>
