the market interpreted the 0.4 percent increase for March as a sign
that inflationary pressures were subsiding. The producer price
index, a measure of inflation at the wholesale level, had risen 1
percent in each of the previous two months.
   Observers said the market is expecting consumer prices to hold
steady at February's 0.4 percent level, or rise only slightly.
   ``If we get that number, I think the market is poised to make a
run upward,'' said Jack Baker, market analyst with Shearson Lehman
Hutton Inc.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks was
up 0.19 at 169.08.
