<FILEID>AP-NR-04-17-89 2108EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-TRW     04-17 0280</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-TRW,0289</SECOND>
<HEAD>TRW Reports Earnings Increase</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CLEVELAND (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rising sales in TRW Inc.'s automotive and
information systems segments helped lead to a first-quarter
earnings increase of 4 percent, the company said Monday.
   TRW said earnings during the period that ended March 31 totaled
$69 million or $1.12 a share, up from $66 million or $1.07 during
the same quarter a year ago.
   ``Each of our major segments reported operating profits equal to
or better than the year-earlier period when we experienced
particularly strong results,'' said Joseph T. Gorman, chairman and
chief executive officer. ``This quarter's earnings improvement was
attained in what we believe was a much tougher competitive
environment.''
   TRW said sales in its space and defense segment dropped 5
percent from $815 to $775 million because of previously announced
program changes and reductions. However, operating profit in that
segment rose nearly 2 percent from $58 million to $59 million, the
company said.
   Sales in the automotive segment rose 10 percent from $787
million to $868 million, TRW said, attributing the increase to
improved business in North America, Europe, Brazil and Japan.
Operating profit in the segment remained at $745 million, TRW said.
   In the information systems segment, sales rose 12 percent from
$126 million to $141 million, TRW said. It noted particularly
strong performances in the consumer credit reporting and
image-based data processing businesses. Operating profit rose 51
percent from $9 million to $13 million in information systems, the
company said.
   TRW, which provides high technology produces and services, said
sales overall for the quarter dropped 1 percent from $1.8 billion
to $1.79 billion. Excluding sales for businesses divested last
year, sales rose 4 percent, TRW said.
</TEXT>
